#. [modification]: id=non_fatal_wounds
#: main/_main.cfg:9
msgid "Non-fatal wounds"
msgstr ""

#. [modification]: id=non_fatal_wounds
#: main/_main.cfg:10
msgid ""
"Units killed during a scenario are instead merely wounded, and can be recalled in later scenarios.\n"
"\n"
"This does not protect your heroes — you’ll still lose if any character who has to survive is wounded. The enemy isn’t going to miss the chance of finishing the battle by letting a leader escape."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: main/utils/campaign_LoW.cfg:35
msgid "Non-Fatal Wounds: in all of mainline Wesnoth, this scenario is probably the most evil act by the player’s own side. The scenario is called Costly Revenge, and for the story it’s meant to be costly to the elves as well as these innocent saurians."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: main/utils/campaign_LoW.cfg:37
msgid "Disable Non-Fatal Wounds and let the story proceed as expected"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: main/utils/campaign_LoW.cfg:46
msgid "Let all the elves survive"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Shynal
#: main/utils/campaign_SotA.cfg:24
msgid "Ow, that was close. I’ll rest until the next battle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Carcyn
#: main/utils/campaign_SotA.cfg:33
msgid "You could have brought her back anyway, right?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ras-Tabahn
#. without this mod, she's brought back as a walking corpse
#: main/utils/campaign_SotA.cfg:45
msgid "Only in part. She would never have the powers of a lich."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ras-Tabahn
#: main/utils/campaign_SotA.cfg:51
msgid "Maybe as a ghost, but even then she would no longer have the powers of a lich."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. generic message which could apply to any scenario where the storyline already explains why even the surviving units don't reappear later in the campaign
#: main/utils/campaigns.cfg:44
#: main/utils/campaigns.cfg:56
msgid "The non-fatal wound modification is disabled for this scenario."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: main/utils/campaigns.cfg:84
msgid "The non-fatal wound modification might work unusually with this campaign. The recall lists change during the campaign, and units that are non-fatally wounded may reappear on the wrong recall list."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. For this scenario, the objective is to avoid deaths for as long as possible, the scenario ends when any unit perishes.
#: main/utils/campaigns.cfg:95
msgid "The non-fatal wound modification does not affect the objectives for this scenario. The unit survives, but still triggers the same events as if it died."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: main/utils/nfw_main.cfg:61
msgid "Argh, I’m wounded"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: main/utils/nfw_main.cfg:62
msgid "female^Argh, I’m wounded"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: main/utils/nfw_main.cfg:66
msgid ""
"With this modification enabled, units are merely wounded instead of killed. If you win this scenario then they will be added to your recall list.\n"
"\n"
"This does not apply to any unit that the objectives require you to keep alive. Even if they say they’re only wounded, the enemy will give your heroes no chance."
msgstr ""

